  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This package conforms to ProfileMinimal; a sha256 content hash is present but the ed25519 signature has not yet been applied — the signature workflow is pending organisational sign-off. Structural integrity is therefore unverifiable until the signature field is populated (W-SI-01). Full 13-factor assessment is included; seven factors were assessed (all with achieved levels below required levels at MRL 5) and six factors remain flagged as epistemic gaps.",
